<para id="element-34">In accordance with the guiding principle as stated earlier, we apply the rule that the result of multiplication or division should have same numbers of significant numbers as that of the measured value with least significant numbers. 
</para>
<para id="element-35">The measured value of volume has the least “2” numbers of significant figures. In accordance with the rule, the result of multiplication is, therefore, limited to two significant digits. The value after rounding off is : 
</para>
<para id="element-36">
<m:math display="block">
  <m:mrow>
    <m:mo>⇒</m:mo>
    <m:mi>m</m:mi>
