<section id="section-5">
<title>Scientific notation</title>
<para id="element-55">Scientific notation uses representation in terms of powers of 10. The representation follows the simple construct as given here :
</para>
<para id="element-582"><m:math display="block">
  <m:mrow>
    <m:mi>x</m:mi>
    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
    <m:mi>a</m:mi>
    <m:msup>
      <m:mn>10</m:mn>
    <m:mi>b</m:mi>
    </m:msup>
  </m:mrow>
</m:math>
</para><para id="element-56">where “a” falls between “1” and “10” and “b” is positive or negative integer. The range of “a” as specified ensures that there is only one digit to the left of decimal. For example, the value of 1 standard atmospheric pressure is :
</para>
<para id="element-57">
<m:math display="block">
